WEBVTT

00:01.168 --> 00:03.868
(truck rumbles loudly,
horn blasts)

00:05.840 --> 00:07.239
<i> Adult mark: They say breakfast</i>

00:07.374 --> 00:09.508
<i> Is the most important meal</i>
<i> of the day,</i>

00:09.510 --> 00:12.444
<i>But seeing how the median age</i>
<i> in our house was 68,</i>

00:12.579 --> 00:14.913
<i> Our breakfast of champions</i>
<i> was pills.</i>

00:17.184 --> 00:19.951
Pop: Oh.
(pills rattle)

00:19.987 --> 00:22.187
Blues before yellows.

00:22.189 --> 00:25.858
Yellows and reds before pinks,
and then whites.

00:25.860 --> 00:28.393
- No. Yellow and red,
then blue.

00:28.429 --> 00:30.262
Pink one after you eat.

00:30.264 --> 00:33.131
White ones are for mark.
- (heavy exhale) jesus.

00:33.200 --> 00:35.467
<i> Adult mark: Pop didn't have</i>
<i> much faith in pills.</i>

00:35.536 --> 00:37.936
<i> He preferred the home remedies</i>
<i> he grew up with.</i>

00:38.005 --> 00:39.471
- (burps and sighs)

00:39.507 --> 00:41.406
- (gasping)

00:41.408 --> 00:43.475
- Asthma's not real.

00:43.544 --> 00:46.912
What you need is a bread
poultice. Here.

00:46.914 --> 00:48.746
<i> Adult mark: Ah, the bread</i>
<i> poultice.</i>

00:48.783 --> 00:50.215
<i>Pop's answer to every ailment</i>

00:50.251 --> 00:52.350
<i>From hangnail to gunshot wound.</i>

00:52.420 --> 00:54.553
<i> Once hardened,</i>
<i> it would supposedly</i>

00:54.555 --> 00:56.187
<i> Draw out the sickness.</i>

00:56.223 --> 00:57.956
- (licks) ooh!

00:57.958 --> 01:00.024
Ooh, that would be lovely
with a nice cup of tea.

01:00.061 --> 01:01.293
Hmm.

01:01.428 --> 01:03.228
<i> Adult mark: Mostly it just</i>
<i> ruined your shirt.</i>

01:03.230 --> 01:05.464
(grossed out) eh.

01:05.466 --> 01:07.633
- They don't work by starin'
at 'em.

01:07.635 --> 01:09.568
- Well, how do we know
they work at all?

01:09.570 --> 01:11.570
- 'cause I'm still looking
at your hoary mug.

01:11.572 --> 01:13.305
- Hmm.
- Uh, mary?
- Hmm?

01:13.440 --> 01:15.841
- Can I talk to you about
the door for a minute?

01:15.910 --> 01:17.576
<i> (footsteps recede)</i>

01:19.112 --> 01:20.812
Are you sure you don't want me
to come with ya

01:20.881 --> 01:22.247
To the hospital--
- oh, shh-shh-shh!

01:22.283 --> 01:24.182
(hushed) I'll be fine.

01:24.251 --> 01:26.318
Very routine operation,
they said.

01:26.387 --> 01:28.220
Besides, the boys
need you here.

01:28.355 --> 01:30.922
- Look, I'm not very good
at this kinda thing, but...

01:30.958 --> 01:33.258
Come back to me in one piece.

01:34.395 --> 01:36.261
Well, you know, minus the piece

01:36.263 --> 01:38.497
They're gonna cut out o' ya
or whatever.

01:38.499 --> 01:40.064
- I will do that.

01:40.101 --> 01:41.967
<i> Adult mark: The old man was</i>
<i> as smooth as sandpaper...</i>

01:41.969 --> 01:43.669
- (small laugh)

01:43.671 --> 01:45.871
<i> And half as comforting.</i>

01:46.006 --> 01:47.272
<i> Mary: Eat your breakfast now</i>

01:47.341 --> 01:49.407
So you can take your pills
that go with food.

01:49.477 --> 01:51.309
- What's going on?

01:51.311 --> 01:53.411
- Oh, it's nothin'
to worry about, mark.

01:53.447 --> 01:55.380
I just have to go into
the hospital is all.

01:55.516 --> 01:58.417
- Oh! Can I go with you!
I love a good hospital visit.

01:58.419 --> 02:01.019
Who're we gonna see?
Mm. Doesn't matter,

02:01.021 --> 02:02.721
I'll wear a suit either way.

02:02.790 --> 02:05.524
- No, mark, your mother's
going in for a small surgery.

02:05.659 --> 02:07.359
(cupboard bangs shut)
so, hey, you're lucky,

02:07.428 --> 02:09.895
You get to stay with me.
Mary: (clears throat)

02:09.964 --> 02:11.930
- Mary, somebody's got
to tell the boy.

02:13.701 --> 02:15.833
- Remember, the tall cans
are for you crowd,

02:15.870 --> 02:18.370
The short ones are for the cat,
hmm?

02:18.372 --> 02:21.506
- Are you dying?
- Oh no, mark. No.

02:21.509 --> 02:23.642
Don't be foolish, hmm?

02:23.644 --> 02:25.444
<i> Pop: Well, I'm dying,</i>
<i> your father's dying,</i>

02:25.446 --> 02:27.579
The cat's dying, the whole
bloody house is dying,

02:27.615 --> 02:29.847
But your mother will
outlive us all.

02:29.884 --> 02:32.384
(horn honks outside)
taxi's here!

02:32.386 --> 02:34.319
- Wha-- uh, you're going
right now?!

02:34.321 --> 02:36.054
You're not even dressed!

02:36.056 --> 02:38.022
<i> - Ah, what do I need to be</i>
<i> dressed for, hmm?</i>

02:38.058 --> 02:40.158
Only gonna to be puttin' on
a robe as soon as I get there.

02:41.862 --> 02:44.596
Oh, mark, you're a big boy now.

02:45.633 --> 02:47.599
Look, you're in charge, okay?

02:47.734 --> 02:49.601
Now you just keep an eye
on everything here

02:49.670 --> 02:51.403
While I'm gone,

02:51.472 --> 02:54.072
And I'll come back fit
as a fiddle.

02:54.208 --> 02:55.807
Give us a hug, huh?

02:55.943 --> 02:57.308
Yeah.

02:59.213 --> 03:00.645
You be a good boy.

03:01.815 --> 03:03.548
<i> Adult mark: I was the man</i>
<i> of the house now,</i>

03:03.551 --> 03:05.617
<i> But our house didn't need</i>
<i> another man;</i>

03:05.653 --> 03:07.352
<i> It needed a mom.</i>

03:07.421 --> 03:09.388
- Hey, we've got tinned
spaghetti

03:09.523 --> 03:11.990
Or purr-fect feast.

03:12.059 --> 03:13.358
You know, with a name
like that,

03:13.360 --> 03:17.095
I am leaning purr-fect feast.

03:17.097 --> 03:20.531
♪♪♪

03:20.568 --> 03:24.102
♪♪♪

03:24.104 --> 03:25.270
- No.

03:25.405 --> 03:27.005
<i> (indistinct chatter)</i>

03:27.041 --> 03:28.473
<i>Fox: Wanna know your fortune?</i>

03:30.110 --> 03:32.844
- What's the point? We're all
just gonna die anyway.

03:32.846 --> 03:35.447
- So... That's a no.

03:35.516 --> 03:37.949
What's your problem?

03:38.018 --> 03:40.586
- My mom's having surgery,
but I don't know what kind.

03:40.721 --> 03:43.054
- You're so weird. How can you
not know something like that?

03:43.090 --> 03:46.391
- They don't want me to worry,
which makes me worried.

03:46.460 --> 03:49.127
<i> Adult mark: I was used</i>
<i> to hospitals and even wakes,</i>

03:49.129 --> 03:51.930
<i> But the thought of losing</i>
<i> my mother terrified me.</i>

03:52.065 --> 03:53.898
<i> Not that my friends noticed.</i>

03:53.968 --> 03:56.034
- Pick a colour.

03:56.103 --> 03:58.169
- Uh... Red.
- R-e-d.

03:58.239 --> 04:00.371
Pick a number.

04:01.408 --> 04:04.409
- Four.
- One, two, three, four.

04:04.411 --> 04:07.145
Now, read your fortune,
dumbass.

04:07.147 --> 04:10.048
(paper rustles and crinkles)

04:10.117 --> 04:13.018
- "you're dead." ha!
What does that mean?

04:14.088 --> 04:15.620
- If I catch you,

04:15.623 --> 04:17.522
Then you're gonna be the one
in the hospital.

04:17.558 --> 04:19.424
Well?

04:19.426 --> 04:21.225
- (nervous grunt) mark!

04:21.262 --> 04:22.894
<i> Adult mark: I needed friends</i>
<i> my own age.</i>

04:23.030 --> 04:24.830
<i> - (pensive exhale)</i>
<i> - I needed pop.</i>

04:24.832 --> 04:26.431
(pop hums along to a sea shanty
on the radio)

04:26.433 --> 04:29.100
(sizzling)

04:29.169 --> 04:31.536
<i> (door bangs shut)</i>

04:32.906 --> 04:35.040
- Ugh! What stinks?
- Mm-hmm!

04:35.175 --> 04:36.974
Supper. Ready.

04:37.011 --> 04:38.643
(chuckles to himself)

04:40.647 --> 04:42.614
<i> Mark: Is that spaghetti</i>
<i> in the cat bowl?</i>

04:42.683 --> 04:45.083
- Mm-hmm.
- Then what's in there?

04:45.218 --> 04:46.918
- Canmash.

04:46.987 --> 04:49.688
- What's that?
- Well, go into the cupboard,

04:49.757 --> 04:51.523
Get all the cans I can,

04:51.592 --> 04:54.593
And mash 'em all together.
Delicious!

04:54.728 --> 04:57.863
Ah, mike, here. Try that.

04:57.998 --> 04:59.997
- Ah, looks good, pop.
- Yeah, yeah, good.

05:00.034 --> 05:02.200
Mm-hmm.
- (eating sounds)

05:02.336 --> 05:04.202
- (horrified gasp)

05:04.204 --> 05:07.205
- How is it?
Come on, one to ten.

05:07.207 --> 05:09.273
(eating noisily)
- ten.

05:09.310 --> 05:11.076
<i> Adult mark: The choices were</i>
<i> clear:</i>

05:11.211 --> 05:13.177
<i>Starvation or food poisoning.</i>

05:14.214 --> 05:15.947
<i>(distant siren wail approaches)</i>

05:17.851 --> 05:20.151
- Mm-hmm.
All good, girl.

05:20.220 --> 05:21.820
- (relieved sigh)

05:21.889 --> 05:24.823
My goodness, connie,
you have got a gentle touch.

05:24.825 --> 05:26.625
- (chuckles)
- it's more like a spa

05:26.760 --> 05:28.894
Than a hospital 'round here.

05:28.896 --> 05:30.629
Sin to say, but...

05:30.764 --> 05:33.030
Sometimes it's nice to be away
from the family.

05:33.167 --> 05:35.233
- Girl, I knows all too much
about it.

05:35.369 --> 05:37.502
I got two boys,
and that's enough.

05:37.637 --> 05:39.671
- Oh, I got the same.
- Oh, really?

05:39.673 --> 05:41.573
- Mm. Truth be told though,

05:41.642 --> 05:43.709
The boys are not the hard part,
it's the--

05:43.844 --> 05:45.777
- The men? Hmm.
- Yes.

05:45.813 --> 05:47.445
- I got one of them too.
- Mm...

05:47.514 --> 05:49.381
Both: (chuckle)

05:49.383 --> 05:52.049
- Well, I suppose it'll all
be okay.

05:52.086 --> 05:54.352
The worst part is they're
just...

05:54.388 --> 05:56.121
Well, there isn't anyone
I can really talk to

05:56.256 --> 05:57.688
About it at home, so...

05:59.960 --> 06:02.827
- It'll be okay, believe me.

06:04.198 --> 06:06.531
I knows all too much about it.

06:06.533 --> 06:08.866
- Yeah. Hmm.

06:08.902 --> 06:11.202
- Now you get to put your feet
up for once!

06:11.271 --> 06:13.872
(cart rattles)
- oh my... (gasps)

06:13.874 --> 06:16.340
Maclean's, chatelaine, owl -

06:16.377 --> 06:18.476
<i> Mark loves that one.</i>
<i> - Mm-hmm.</i>

06:18.478 --> 06:20.478
- I think I'll go
with chatelaine.

06:20.547 --> 06:23.682
- Proper damn thing!
- Thank you.

06:23.684 --> 06:26.017
- Want a cup o' tea?
- Oh yes, dear.

06:26.153 --> 06:28.085
Where's the kettle?
- Oh, no.

06:28.122 --> 06:30.889
No, you lie down.
Read your magazine.

06:30.891 --> 06:32.424
- What?
- I'll get it for ya.

06:32.559 --> 06:34.225
- Oh!

06:34.261 --> 06:35.894
Connie, I'm movin' in
for good.

06:35.896 --> 06:37.496
- You're welcome to it.
- (chuckles)

06:37.631 --> 06:39.564
<i> Announcement: Dr. Patterson</i>
<i> to the er, please.</i>

06:39.566 --> 06:41.299
<i> That's dr. Patterson--</i>

06:41.435 --> 06:42.968
(rotary phone dial rattles)

06:43.103 --> 06:45.103
- Pop, ya gotta take
your pills!

06:47.441 --> 06:49.174
(pill bottles rattle)

06:49.243 --> 06:51.742
- Hmph. Bloody drug pusher.

06:52.913 --> 06:54.913
- Uh, mary critch's room,
please?

06:54.915 --> 06:57.182
<i> Pop: This is what I'm after.</i>

06:57.317 --> 07:00.885
Mustard and bread.
Can't beat it.

07:02.055 --> 07:03.655
<i> Mike sr.: Hello, mary?</i>
<i> Mary: (muffled) mark?</i>

07:03.724 --> 07:05.390
- What?
- Mark?

07:05.392 --> 07:07.258
- Let me have that again.
The line's very bad.

07:07.294 --> 07:08.893
<i> - (muffled) what the frig?</i>

07:08.929 --> 07:11.596
- You go under the knife
at 9:00 a.M., you say?

07:11.598 --> 07:14.065
- My god!
- Good god!

07:14.101 --> 07:16.400
This line is terrible!

07:16.437 --> 07:17.936
I'm gonna have to call
the phone company.

07:17.938 --> 07:19.738
I mean, what the hell
am I paying for?

07:19.740 --> 07:22.007
- (indistinct comment)
- what does dr. Fisher say?

07:22.142 --> 07:24.275
<i> Adult mark: Kids overhear more</i>
<i> than their parents think,</i>

07:24.311 --> 07:26.744
<i> Especially when everything</i>
<i> they say is shouted.</i>

07:26.780 --> 07:29.681
<i> I listened to every word</i>
<i> for a glimmer of truth.</i>

07:29.816 --> 07:32.149
- A full hysterectomy?
- I was a good bit surprised.

07:32.186 --> 07:33.952
(indistinct comment)
- now don't worry about us.

07:33.954 --> 07:36.354
We have things well in hand.
You just rest.

07:36.423 --> 07:38.289
(line goes quiet,
plungers click)

07:38.358 --> 07:40.826
Hello?! Mary? Mary? Hello?!

07:42.896 --> 07:44.529
She's dead.
- (gasps)

07:47.434 --> 07:49.634
- Uh, the line.
The line's dead.

07:49.703 --> 07:51.903
Terrible line.
(handset clunks loudly)

07:51.939 --> 07:54.906
That was your mother.
She's having a wonderful time.

07:54.942 --> 07:57.275
<i> (cat meows)</i>

07:57.410 --> 07:59.444
Cat hasn't even touched
her noodles.

07:59.513 --> 08:01.379
Puss! Puthy, puthy, puthy!

08:01.381 --> 08:03.982
<i> Adult mark: Misty was our cat.</i>
<i>She only appeared for feedings.</i>

08:03.984 --> 08:06.450
<i>Like everything in our house,</i>
<i> she was old.</i>

08:07.855 --> 08:10.388
<i> Dad loved the cat almost</i>
<i> as much as it hated him.</i>

08:10.524 --> 08:12.357
(misty hisses)
- agh! She's a bloody lynx!

08:12.492 --> 08:14.226
<i> Misty: (angry meow)</i>

08:14.361 --> 08:15.826
<i> Mike sr.: Goddamn cat.</i>

08:17.664 --> 08:20.598
<i> - Pop?</i>
<i> - Yes, sir.</i>

08:21.802 --> 08:24.402
- Am I gonna have to have
a hysternmectomy one day?

08:24.537 --> 08:26.270
- Mm. Maybe.

08:27.808 --> 08:30.275
Maybe not.

08:30.344 --> 08:32.077
Probably not.

08:32.212 --> 08:33.978
- How do you know?

08:35.415 --> 08:40.285
- You know, sometimes a flower
loses its petals... Mm.

08:41.488 --> 08:43.021
Mm...

08:43.090 --> 08:44.823
<i> No pollen then.</i>

08:44.958 --> 08:47.359
<i> Bees come buzzin' around</i>

08:47.361 --> 08:49.427
<i> Lookin' for this, that</i>
<i> and the other,</i>

08:49.496 --> 08:52.430
But you're not gonna get stung
by a bee,

08:52.432 --> 08:54.432
'cause if they sting you,

08:54.434 --> 08:57.268
Then they have to rip
their own arse out.

08:57.337 --> 08:59.303
<i> And if they rip</i>
<i> their own arse out,</i>

08:59.339 --> 09:01.172
<i> Well, then...</i>

09:01.174 --> 09:02.640
<i> They just die.</i>

09:03.710 --> 09:05.977
That's what's wrong
with your mother.

09:07.113 --> 09:08.980
More or less. Mm...

09:09.016 --> 09:11.315
<i>Adult mark: I didn't know why</i>
<i> pop needed all those pills,</i>

09:11.351 --> 09:13.250
<i> But it was becoming clear</i>
<i> that he needed them</i>

09:13.287 --> 09:15.320
<i>More than the bread poultice.</i>

09:15.455 --> 09:18.155
- Ah, they wouldn't let me in
with flat feet.

09:19.726 --> 09:21.459
Oh...

09:21.528 --> 09:24.028
Those bouncing bombs...

09:25.299 --> 09:27.132
Amazing.

09:27.267 --> 09:30.135
Skip, skip, skip.

09:32.072 --> 09:33.871
<i> Hit the dam,</i>

09:33.907 --> 09:35.673
<i> Sank,</i>

09:35.742 --> 09:37.809
<i> Boom.</i>

09:37.944 --> 09:39.877
<i> (chuckles)</i>

09:39.913 --> 09:41.946
<i> Ah, the bastards.</i>

09:41.949 --> 09:43.948
(grunts)

09:43.984 --> 09:45.583
<i> - Pop?</i>

09:45.586 --> 09:47.685
Did you take your pills?

09:47.754 --> 09:50.688
- Okay.

09:50.757 --> 09:53.491
Mm...
- Night, pop.

09:54.895 --> 09:56.361
<i> - Mm...</i>

09:56.496 --> 09:57.928
Good cat.

10:00.033 --> 10:02.567
<i> (dog barks in the distance,</i>
<i> birds chirp)</i>

10:02.569 --> 10:04.502
(kettle whistles)
radio: And now mike critch

10:04.504 --> 10:06.771
With the vcom news!
- Mike! You up?

10:06.773 --> 10:09.841
Radio: Were called the scene...
- Your bus'll be here soon.

10:10.911 --> 10:12.743
Radio: Two youths...
- Mike?!

10:12.779 --> 10:14.612
- I'm gone.
(front door shuts)

10:14.615 --> 10:16.915
- Oh, you give and you give,
but they just don't care.

10:16.917 --> 10:19.050
<i>Radio: They were disappointed</i>
<i> with the fried chicken...</i>

10:19.086 --> 10:20.919
(pill bottles rattle)
- pop?!

10:22.356 --> 10:24.322
Pop?!

10:24.324 --> 10:26.390
Can no one answer me
this morning?!

10:26.426 --> 10:28.392
<i>Radio: The officers were able</i>
<i> to follow...</i>

10:28.428 --> 10:29.760
- Am I talking to thin air?!

10:31.198 --> 10:32.963
(pop grunts softly)
pop?

10:35.001 --> 10:37.535
Pop!

10:37.537 --> 10:39.237
Pop!
(pop grunts softly)

10:40.340 --> 10:42.940
Pop!
- (grunts softly)

10:42.942 --> 10:44.809
- (grunts of effort)
- (grunts softly)

10:44.845 --> 10:46.811
<i> (running footsteps)</i>

10:46.847 --> 10:49.214
(phone clatters,
dial tone drones)

10:49.349 --> 10:50.748
(panting)

10:50.817 --> 10:53.350
(dial rattles)

10:53.387 --> 10:55.252
(line rings,
pop grunts softly)

10:55.288 --> 10:57.588
(phone rings)

10:57.658 --> 11:00.692
- Drive safely. Arrive alive.
Vocm news. Critch speaking.

11:00.694 --> 11:02.627
- It's pop! Come quick!
It's pop.

11:02.629 --> 11:04.596
- Pop? My god, you sound
more like mark.

11:04.731 --> 11:06.131
<i> This is an awfully clear line.</i>

11:06.133 --> 11:07.832
Gonna have to call the phone
company, let 'em know.

11:07.834 --> 11:09.968
- I am mark! Pop's dead!
Come home!

11:11.705 --> 11:13.104
(handset slams down,
door bangs shut)

11:13.239 --> 11:14.906
Pop: Mm-hmm.
(footsteps thud rapidly)

11:14.908 --> 11:17.041
- Oh god...

11:18.478 --> 11:20.244
- You think he's dead?

11:20.313 --> 11:22.580
- No, but... He's gone
all yellow.

11:22.582 --> 11:24.115
<i> - That's just the poultice.</i>

11:24.250 --> 11:25.984
<i> I think he stopped taking</i>
<i> his pills.</i>

11:25.986 --> 11:28.686
I'm too young to be in charge!
First mom's gonna die, now pop.

11:29.990 --> 11:31.856
You shouldn't have left!

11:31.858 --> 11:33.824
And you shouldn't have
let her go!

11:33.860 --> 11:35.793
- Mark! Enough.
(breathing rapidly)

11:35.862 --> 11:37.662
Call 9-1-1.

11:37.731 --> 11:39.263
- You think we need
an ambulance?

11:39.265 --> 11:40.999
- We need two.

11:41.001 --> 11:43.334
I'm having a heart attack.

11:43.336 --> 11:45.269
(running footsteps)

11:45.338 --> 11:47.072
<i> - Don't worry,</i>
<i> I'm getting help!</i>

11:50.677 --> 11:52.010
<i> (wheelchair creaks)</i>

11:52.145 --> 11:54.179
- Thank you, connie,
you're such a luv.

11:54.181 --> 11:56.614
(toilet flushes)
- oh, hello, mary.

11:56.683 --> 11:58.750
- Jesus! (gasps) you nearly
gave me a heart attack!

11:58.752 --> 12:00.451
(curtain rattles back)

12:00.454 --> 12:03.154
- Uh, well, mike already
beat you to it.

12:03.156 --> 12:05.556
- Oh my god, are you okay?

12:05.625 --> 12:07.158
- Yes, I'm fine.

12:07.194 --> 12:09.060
I just had a touch
of a heart attack.

12:09.129 --> 12:11.329
I got a bit startled
when I found pop dead.

12:11.398 --> 12:13.497
- Uh, dea--
- I'm not dead!

12:13.533 --> 12:15.967
The doctor said I've got
at least ten years left

12:15.969 --> 12:17.969
If I stop smoking.

12:17.971 --> 12:19.838
He put me down for five.

12:19.973 --> 12:21.940
- When's your surgery?
- Oh.

12:21.942 --> 12:24.909
- She already had it,
and she's doing well, but...

12:24.911 --> 12:26.911
You know, this isn't
a legion bingo hall.

12:26.947 --> 12:28.846
Can everybody please just
go back to their rooms?

12:28.915 --> 12:30.848
- It's fine, connie,
I don't mind.

12:30.917 --> 12:32.383
Could you just give us
a moment?

12:32.419 --> 12:34.052
- Okay.

12:34.187 --> 12:37.188
(indistinct chatter,
wheelchair creaks by)

12:37.224 --> 12:40.724
- I leave you arseholes alone
for 36 hours

12:40.761 --> 12:43.127
And you wind up
in the hospital?!

12:43.130 --> 12:44.896
Who is minding the boys?

12:44.965 --> 12:47.432
- You're the one put mark
in charge.

12:47.434 --> 12:49.934
- Only good choice I made
this weekend, apparently!

12:49.936 --> 12:53.004
Jesus this hurts!
(pained grunt)

12:53.139 --> 12:55.673
(blows out her breath)
- this is delicious.

12:55.675 --> 12:58.209
We should get this at home.

12:58.344 --> 13:00.344
(rock music plays,
mike jr. And friends laugh)

13:00.413 --> 13:02.546
Mark: Everyone we hold dear
is in hospital

13:02.548 --> 13:04.282
And you throw a party!

13:04.284 --> 13:05.950
Unbelievable.

13:05.986 --> 13:07.952
- There's two people.

13:07.954 --> 13:09.987
We-we're playing cards,
get lost!

13:09.989 --> 13:13.057
- Hmph! Can't get lost
in my own home now, can I?

13:13.059 --> 13:15.026
That's what this house is,
by the way,

13:15.095 --> 13:16.961
A home.

13:16.963 --> 13:18.530
(sighs)

13:18.665 --> 13:20.564
Which we'll treat with respect,
I imagine.

13:20.600 --> 13:22.233
(rock music plays)

13:22.368 --> 13:24.635
<i> (sighs heavily,</i>
<i> wrappers crinkle)</i>

13:26.173 --> 13:28.439
Mike jr.: Hey! Put that down!
It's a strobe light.

13:28.441 --> 13:31.242
We're gonna listen to some
floyd when it gets dark

13:31.278 --> 13:33.244
And use it
to trip-ip-ip-ip-ip-ip.

13:33.280 --> 13:35.613
Friends: (laugh)

13:35.748 --> 13:37.916
<i> Adult mark: My brother was</i>
<i> practically turning our home</i>

13:38.051 --> 13:39.984
<i> Into an opium den.</i>

13:41.054 --> 13:43.221
- Mark. Go.

13:46.860 --> 13:48.192
- Hmph!

13:48.228 --> 13:49.827
(rock music plays loudly)

13:51.464 --> 13:53.064
- (sighs) I've completely
lost control.

13:53.199 --> 13:55.066
Mike's having a party.

13:55.135 --> 13:57.034
There's a musician here!

13:57.070 --> 13:59.003
- Cool! Can I come?

13:59.005 --> 14:01.272
- Ritchie, homework.

14:01.274 --> 14:03.007
- Ah! Mrs. Perez!

14:03.076 --> 14:04.876
How are you, ma'am?

14:04.878 --> 14:06.777
- I'm fine, mark.

14:06.847 --> 14:08.979
Ritchie needs to finish
his homework.

14:09.015 --> 14:11.282
No phone.
- 'kay.

14:11.351 --> 14:13.150
<i> Mike jr.: (yells) come on!</i>

14:13.186 --> 14:15.353
- There's the sober perspective
I'm after.

14:15.422 --> 14:17.488
Good call, mrs. Perez.

14:17.624 --> 14:19.357
Without a firm hand
at the wheel,

14:19.426 --> 14:21.158
It all comes crumbling down.

14:21.294 --> 14:22.993
- Thank you, mark.

14:23.029 --> 14:25.796
- No, (chuckles)
thank you, mrs. Perez.

14:27.033 --> 14:29.033
(handset clicks)

14:29.102 --> 14:31.669
(handset clatters,
mike and his friends laugh)

14:31.738 --> 14:33.537
(dial tone drones)
- hello?

14:36.176 --> 14:38.709
(busy signal beeps)
- (sighs) still busy.

14:38.778 --> 14:40.378
(handset clicks)
my god,

14:40.447 --> 14:43.047
I can't even enjoy an operation
to myself with you crowd.

14:43.049 --> 14:46.317
Pop: Uh, wait. Have you got
many stitches?

14:46.319 --> 14:48.019
Because, you know,
a bread poultice

14:48.154 --> 14:49.887
Will see you right.

14:49.890 --> 14:52.089
- You go away with
your bay voodoo.

14:53.326 --> 14:56.261
Mike, you think that...
Dick would look in on them?

14:56.396 --> 14:58.796
- Mike is 16 years old,

14:58.798 --> 15:00.731
And mark is older than I am.

15:00.800 --> 15:02.533
- You're just full of comfort,
aren't ya?

15:02.602 --> 15:04.001
- (sucks teeth)

15:04.070 --> 15:05.637
- Jesus!

15:05.772 --> 15:09.807
- Fruit in syrup - gorgeous!
100 percent.

15:09.809 --> 15:11.409
(toast pops up,
rock music plays)

15:11.411 --> 15:13.344
<i> Adult mark: Like mrs. Perez,</i>
<i> I came to realize</i>

15:13.380 --> 15:15.879
<i> That someone had to put</i>
<i> the "hold" in household.</i>

15:15.916 --> 15:17.982
<i> It was up to me</i>
<i> to hold the fort.</i>

15:18.117 --> 15:19.817
(mark hums to the music,
mike's friends shout)

15:19.819 --> 15:21.486
<i> When it came to cooking,</i>

15:21.621 --> 15:23.988
<i> I really put the boy</i>
<i> in chef boyardee.</i>

15:24.123 --> 15:26.090
<i> (loud knock at the door)</i>
<i> friend: What're ya doin'?</i>

15:26.092 --> 15:28.359
- The door?
Oh, good god!

15:28.395 --> 15:30.161
It's 6:30 at night!

15:30.230 --> 15:32.230
<i> Mike jr.: Oh! I got it!</i>

15:32.232 --> 15:34.765
<i> Adult mark: In the '80s,</i>
<i> certain cab companies</i>

15:34.767 --> 15:36.768
<i> Would deliver beer</i>
<i> right to your door,</i>

15:36.770 --> 15:38.302
<i> No questions asked.</i>

15:38.338 --> 15:40.238
- Yes! Thank you!
Keep the change.

15:40.373 --> 15:42.006
(door bangs shut,
beer bottles clink)

15:42.141 --> 15:44.308
- You bought beer?
- Go back in the kitchen.

15:46.379 --> 15:47.845
- Good god!

15:48.949 --> 15:50.381
(kisses box, friend laughs)

15:50.450 --> 15:52.583
- Let's see.
- Let's go!

15:52.585 --> 15:54.452
- I don't believe you!

15:54.454 --> 15:56.721
You're going full belushi
on me.

15:56.790 --> 15:58.523
<i> It's like...</i>

15:58.525 --> 16:00.725
The chateau marmont in here.

16:00.860 --> 16:03.894
You don't even care about mom,
or dad! Or pop--

16:03.964 --> 16:06.197
- Hey, of course I'm worried
about them, but...

16:06.199 --> 16:08.265
There's nothing I can do
about it.

16:09.336 --> 16:11.502
And I'm not a bad guy,
you know?

16:12.872 --> 16:15.139
This is why no one wants
to hang out with you.

16:15.175 --> 16:17.308
(cap clatters)
try being a kid for once.

16:18.478 --> 16:20.144
<i> Adult mark: He was right.</i>

16:20.146 --> 16:23.347
<i>I was driving the only family</i>
<i> I had left away from me.</i>

16:24.484 --> 16:30.087
♪♪♪

16:30.156 --> 16:33.690
(strobe light clicks on
and whirs)

16:33.727 --> 16:36.360
- Is that all it does?
- Well, I think it's cool!

16:36.363 --> 16:38.262
Yeah!

16:38.331 --> 16:40.330
- I think it's kinda crap.

16:40.367 --> 16:42.066
- Trippy!

16:42.201 --> 16:44.168
Trip, trip. Come on!

16:44.170 --> 16:46.170
Come on! Trip!

16:46.172 --> 16:48.172
<i> Adult mark: Mike wanted me</i>
<i> to act my age,</i>

16:48.241 --> 16:50.174
<i> But I had never been</i>
<i> my age before.</i>

16:50.176 --> 16:52.476
- Trip, trip, trip, trip!

16:52.512 --> 16:54.812
(mark dances to the rock music
playing)

16:54.814 --> 16:56.814
- Hey, that's too close.

16:56.850 --> 16:58.216
- Who's the party pooper now,
huh?

16:58.218 --> 17:00.151
- Mark, that's too close!

17:00.286 --> 17:01.718
<i> Adult mark: I don't suppose</i>
<i> there's a good time</i>

17:01.755 --> 17:03.720
<i> To discover you're</i>
<i> an epileptic...</i>

17:03.757 --> 17:05.322
- (grunts)
(heavy thud)

17:05.392 --> 17:07.991
- Mark!
- (grunting)

17:09.596 --> 17:12.496
<i> Adult mark: But this had to be</i>
<i> one of the worst.</i>

17:15.401 --> 17:17.068
P strums)

17:17.070 --> 17:19.604
- (echoey) mark, honey,
are you okay?

17:20.973 --> 17:23.608
- Uh... Where am I?

17:23.610 --> 17:25.376
Who are you?

17:25.378 --> 17:27.278
- (echoey) god,
he doesn't even know us.

17:27.347 --> 17:29.447
Mark, it's mom!

17:29.516 --> 17:31.248
<i> Adult mark: I woke up after</i>
<i> my seizure</i>

17:31.250 --> 17:33.150
<i>Like dorothy after the tornado.</i>

17:33.219 --> 17:35.286
<i> My brain was fried.</i>

17:35.288 --> 17:38.289
- Are ya on drugs? Huh?
What is it?

17:38.424 --> 17:41.425
The reefer? Smack? Acid?

17:41.461 --> 17:43.561
(angelic harp strums)

17:43.630 --> 17:45.496
- The doctor said
it's epilepsy.

17:45.532 --> 17:47.432
He had a seizure,
that's all.

17:47.567 --> 17:50.168
- Allergic to flashing lights?
Foolishness!

17:50.303 --> 17:53.304
What you need
is a bread poultice.

17:53.439 --> 17:56.240
(angelic harp strums)

17:56.309 --> 17:58.743
Mary: Excuse me, connie?

17:58.745 --> 18:00.678
I need to be discharged
right away.

18:00.747 --> 18:04.248
- But, mary, you're supposed
to stay for one more night.

18:04.250 --> 18:06.184
- I know, girl,
but the only way

18:06.319 --> 18:08.252
I'm gonna get any peace tonight
is if I go home.

18:08.254 --> 18:10.054
<i> Pop: Yeah! Let's get outta</i>
<i> this place.</i>

18:10.123 --> 18:12.823
We were all fine
until we came here!

18:12.826 --> 18:14.191
(machines beep)

18:14.260 --> 18:16.861
- Ohhh... I-I remember this.

18:16.930 --> 18:19.062
You're all crazy,

18:19.099 --> 18:22.232
<i> And, uh, I worry about</i>
<i> losing you a lot</i>

18:23.336 --> 18:25.670
'cause... (inhales)

18:25.805 --> 18:27.171
You're old.

18:27.306 --> 18:29.540
- What? Not that old.

18:29.609 --> 18:32.743
- I love you.
- Aww...

18:32.779 --> 18:35.646
- Well, we're all very fond
of you, too, son.

18:37.117 --> 18:39.617
- (sighs) is there any beer
left?

18:39.619 --> 18:42.019
- Uh, yeah, there he goes...

18:42.155 --> 18:44.222
Not making any sense again.

18:44.357 --> 18:46.290
Silly, silly boy.

18:46.292 --> 18:49.026
Hey, uh... Why don't you all
go get dressed.

18:49.028 --> 18:51.695
I'll keep an eye on mark.
- No, I think I should stay.

18:51.697 --> 18:54.432
- Mom, it's okay, I got him.

18:55.835 --> 18:58.769
<i> Mark: (sighs woozily)</i>
<i> mike sr.: All right.</i>

18:58.771 --> 19:01.038
(footsteps tap lightly)

19:04.177 --> 19:06.110
- I remember you.

19:07.313 --> 19:10.113
You're my brother.

19:10.150 --> 19:12.849
- Welcome back, little brother.

19:12.886 --> 19:14.518
- Hmm...

19:14.554 --> 19:17.921
- Hey, you uh...
You wanna play?

19:17.957 --> 19:19.390
- Yeah.

19:19.392 --> 19:21.258
(grunts)
- all right.

19:21.327 --> 19:23.794
(sighs) war?

19:23.830 --> 19:25.796
- Yeah.
- (chuckles softly)

19:25.798 --> 19:27.665
(cards thump)
♪ come with me...

19:27.734 --> 19:29.800
I got you a birthday present.
(cards thwap)

19:29.936 --> 19:32.470
- Oh, what'd you get me?
- A new strobe light.

19:32.472 --> 19:35.005
(door squeaks open)

19:35.041 --> 19:36.741
- Oh dear...

19:36.876 --> 19:38.742
<i> Adult mark: Despite my</i>
<i> worrying, the grim reaper</i>

19:38.811 --> 19:40.611
<i> Had finally come knocking,</i>

19:40.746 --> 19:43.614
<i> And misty was</i>
<i> the only one home.</i>

19:45.218 --> 19:47.852
<i> Our cat had died,</i>
<i> and the loss for us</i>

19:47.854 --> 19:50.221
<i> Was as indelible as her fur</i>
<i> on the couch.</i>

19:50.223 --> 19:53.156
♪ you will always be...
(dirt thuds, shovels scrape)

19:53.193 --> 19:54.425
♪ home

19:54.427 --> 19:56.059
(shovels thud)

19:58.531 --> 20:00.063
♪ there might be palaces...

20:00.099 --> 20:01.898
- I think somebody should
say something.

20:01.935 --> 20:04.134
♪ ...Where we go

20:05.371 --> 20:07.705
- Uh...

20:07.774 --> 20:11.108
16 years is a long life
for a cat.

20:11.110 --> 20:14.312
She did everything
she was supposed to do -

20:14.447 --> 20:17.481
Ate, crapped, licked herself.

20:19.052 --> 20:21.418
Can't ask for much more
outta life than that.

20:22.722 --> 20:25.256
<i> Good cat.</i>

20:25.258 --> 20:26.757
♪ always be home...

20:26.892 --> 20:29.660
- I never liked her, you know?
(sobs)

20:29.729 --> 20:31.528
It's a sin to say it now,

20:31.564 --> 20:33.530
But she scratched
something awful.

20:35.802 --> 20:38.269
She was family.

20:38.271 --> 20:39.503
<i> Adult mark: That was the first</i>

20:39.639 --> 20:43.173
<i> And last time I ever saw</i>
<i> my mother cry.</i>

20:44.410 --> 20:47.678
- Oh, somebody say something.
It's just a cat.

20:47.747 --> 20:49.413
<i> Adult mark: At the time,</i>
<i> I thought that mom</i>

20:49.415 --> 20:52.316
<i> Was crying for misty,</i>
<i> but looking back,</i>

20:52.451 --> 20:55.086
<i> I think her tears were</i>
<i> for something else she lost.</i>

20:55.088 --> 20:57.754
♪ and you will see
that we always be... ♪

20:57.790 --> 20:59.624
- I still can't remember much,

20:59.759 --> 21:02.125
But did I do a good job
when I was in charge?

21:04.264 --> 21:05.762
- Yeah.

21:05.798 --> 21:07.964
Yeah, you did.

21:08.001 --> 21:10.967
(sentimental music plays,
light pat)

21:11.004 --> 21:13.704
<i> Adult mark: Sometimes,</i>
<i> all you need to carry on</i>

21:13.839 --> 21:16.139
<i> Is someone to help</i>
<i> carry the load.</i>

21:18.645 --> 21:20.911
♪ home...
(hard punch)

21:20.947 --> 21:22.746
- Oh, ho, ho... (laughing)
- hey!

21:24.150 --> 21:31.055
♪♪♪

21:31.124 --> 21:38.062
♪♪♪

21:38.131 --> 21:45.136
♪♪♪

21:45.138 --> 21:52.043
